{# ── DISCLOSURE BANNER · ABOVE THE FOLD (Sheet-7 honest-triage). Canonical .disclosure class
     (03-conversion.css). The inBrief above already states the NOT-Intuit boundary directly under
     the dark hero; this banner makes it unmissable a SECOND time and carries the explicit Intuit
     support link. Honesty is the #1 gate on this hub. ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="qb-support-disclosure">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="disclosure disclosure--warn">
      <svg class="disclosure__icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#A4660A" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 11v5M12 7.5v.3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      <div class="disclosure__body"><strong>TechBrot is an independent accounting firm of Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors. We are not Intuit.</strong> For account, billing, or subscription issues, contact Intuit directly <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">&rarr;</a> &mdash; this team cannot access your Intuit account, change your subscription, reset your login, or fix the QuickBooks software. &ldquo;Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor&rdquo; is a certification this firm holds from Intuit; it does not mean affiliation, endorsement, or sponsorship. What this team does is the accounting work inside your own books. This page is informational; it is not Intuit support.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── TRIAGE · the whole point of the hub: two columns, stated proudly. Left = Intuit's to fix
     (account/billing/subscription/login/2FA/refunds/software-bugs) with the Intuit link. Right =
     independent ProAdvisor work inside your own books. checks-list components, grid-2. ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-triage">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Get to the right help faster</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Two kinds of &ldquo;QuickBooks support.&rdquo;</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most &ldquo;QuickBooks support&rdquo; searches are really one of two jobs. Match yours to the right column &mdash; we&rsquo;d rather route you correctly than book a call that can&rsquo;t help. The account itself is Intuit&rsquo;s; the accounting inside it is ours.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">Intuit&rsquo;s to fix</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Contact Intuit directly for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-support-intuit-list">
          <li>Intuit <strong>account</strong> problems &mdash; access, profile, company-account ownership.</li>
          <li><strong>Billing, subscriptions, renewals, and refunds</strong> &mdash; charges, plan changes, cancellations.</li>
          <li><strong>Login, password, and two-factor (2FA)</strong> resets and lockouts.</li>
          <li><strong>QuickBooks software bugs, outages, and Intuit-side error codes</strong> &mdash; the product itself misbehaving.</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">Go to Intuit support <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">An independent ProAdvisor&rsquo;s work</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">Talk to an independent Certified ProAdvisor for&hellip;</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list" id="qb-support-proadvisor-list">
          <li><strong>File errors and cleanup</strong> &mdash; a broken or messy company file, miscategorized transactions, books behind for months.</li>
          <li><strong>Reconciliation</strong> that won&rsquo;t balance &mdash; bank/credit-card feeds, opening balances, undeposited funds.</li>
          <li><strong>Setup and migration</strong> &mdash; a correct chart of accounts, sales-tax configuration, and Desktop-to-Online or Enterprise moves without data loss.</li>
          <li><strong>Payroll inside your file and CPA-ready books</strong> &mdash; mapping, multi-state tax setup, and statements your CPA can file from.</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Get the free file review <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. #qb-support-hub-summary id carries the speakable selector
     declared in the data module. (H2) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks support, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="qb-support-hub-summary">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SUPPORT SPOKES · buyer-card grid linking ONLY to built/this-wave pages: the flagship
     how-to-contact + independent-help (ship in this proof set), plus the EXISTING speak-expert
     and error-codes. Help-symptom pages that fan out later are described in PROSE below with no
     dead links. (H2 + H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-spokes">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Where to go next</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The support pages that actually help.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Each of these routes a real intent &mdash; honestly. They tell you what Intuit owns and what an independent Certified ProAdvisor does, and they never imply this firm is Intuit.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for s in spokes %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.eyebrow | safe }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading"><a href="{{ s.href }}"{% if s.rel %} rel="{{ s.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ s.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ s.href }}"{% if s.rel %} rel="{{ s.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ s.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── HELP CATEGORIES (PROSE, NO DEAD LINKS) · the symptom-level help pages fan out in a later
     wave; we describe the categories here in prose so the hub reads complete without linking
     pages that don't exist yet. (H2) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-categories">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">More help, on the way</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Common QuickBooks problems we cover.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Beyond the pages above, the most common QuickBooks problems owners bring fall into a few groups, all of them work <strong>inside your own books</strong> rather than the Intuit account: <strong>reconciliation and balance problems</strong> (a register that won&rsquo;t tie out, opening-balance errors, stuck undeposited funds); <strong>data and file health</strong> (a bloated or damaged company file, duplicate transactions, list cleanup); <strong>setup and structure</strong> (a chart of accounts that fights you, classes and locations, sales-tax configuration); <strong>connections and feeds</strong> (bank and credit-card feeds that mis-match or stop syncing); and <strong>payroll inside the file</strong> (wage and tax mapping, multi-state setup, year-end forms reconciled in your books).</p>
      <p>Dedicated guides for these are being added. In the meantime, if the issue is in your file, a Certified ProAdvisor can scope it on the free file review. If the issue is the Intuit account, the subscription, your login, or a software bug, that is Intuit&rsquo;s to fix &mdash; <a href="https://quickbooks.intuit.com/learn-support/" rel="noopener nofollow">contact Intuit directly <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── CALL BREAKOUT · bofu handoff component (honest-triage: file/books problems → us). ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-breakout">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="call-breakout">
      <div>
        <p class="call-breakout__title">A file, books, or error problem &mdash; not an Intuit account issue?</p>
        <p class="call-breakout__sub">A Certified ProAdvisor (independent firm) reviews your own QuickBooks file and scopes the fix in writing, fixed-fee. For Intuit account, billing, or login issues, contact Intuit directly.</p>
      </div>
      <a class="btn btn--primary" href="/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review">Get the free file review</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 6+ Q/A; FIRST = "Is this Intuit's official QuickBooks support?" → No, plainly
     (Sheet-7 mandatory). visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2) ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">QuickBooks support questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="qb-support-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="qb-support-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level (no founder name). David survives only as reviewedBy @id in
     schema. (H2) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="qb-support-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How this hub is kept honest.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>{{ reviewProse | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-18</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-18</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-18 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── RELATED · grid-2 buyer-cards. (H2 + H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="qb-support-related">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where else to go.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading"><a href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.title | safe }}</a></h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ r.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="buyer-card__cta" href="{{ r.href }}"{% if r.rel %} rel="{{ r.rel }}"{% endif %}>{{ r.cta | safe }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
